íŸ@f7baccb4b66a652d7c35397e86c64fc10872fe1c77c85354d606436c350909d8⁄˘Title: title: mktemp
Path: Flags
Content:
``--suffix {string}``
: Append suffix to template; must not contain a slash.
``--tmpdir-path, -p {path}``
: Interpret TEMPLATE relative to tmpdir-path. If tmpdir-path is not set use $TMPDIR.
``--tmpdir, -t``
: Interpret TEMPLATE relative to the system temporary directory. It is implied if template is not provided.
``--directory, -d``
: Create a directory instead of a file.
``--dry``
: Don't create a file and just return the path that would have been created.
íŸ@9e214fe028832e84becc0d2ab02b831894b02441cf72b34b49ca8a76ba8b31c4ŸºTitle: title: mktemp
Path: Parameters
Content:
``template``
: Optional pattern from which the name of the file or directory is derived. Must contain at least three 'X's in last component.
